August delivery climbed 36 points, or 0.7 percent, to 5,110.5 at
9:22 a.m. in  Singapore .  The futures are derived from the 50 stocks on the
underlying S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange
of  India  Ltd. The gauge fell 1.3 percent to 5,072.95 on Aug. 12,
capping a third straight weekly loss. Indiaâ€™s equity markets are
